article.description: — Tre'Von Spillers scored 20 points as Appalachian State beat Austin Peay 78-58 on Sunday.
article.headline: Spillers scores 20, Appalachian State downs Austin Peay 78-58
article.linkText: Spillers scores 20, Appalachian State downs Austin Peay 78-58
article.story: BOONE, N.C. -- — Tre'Von Spillers scored 20 points as Appalachian State beat Austin Peay 78-58 on Sunday. Spillers added seven rebounds for the Mountaineers (4-2). Donovan Gregory scored 17 points, shooting 4 of 5 from the field and 7 for 7 from the line. Jordan Marsh shot 5 for 8, including 3 for 4 from beyond the arc to finish with 13 points. The Governors (3-4) were led in scoring by Demarcus Sharp, who finished with 22 points, five assists and four steals. Austin Peay also got 11 points and two steals from Ja'Monta Black. Dezi Jones also had 10 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
